Repository.
    - GitHub is the Open Source Repository Maintained By Google.

GitHub Operations.

1.Create the Repository Locally.

2. Add the User Credentials to the Repository.

3. Create the Files to the Repository.

4. Commit the Files to the Repository.

5. Create the Branch

6. Merge the Branches

7. Integrating the GitHub to the IDE'S - Ecilipse , WebStrom , Visual Studio.

8. Push the Code to the Cloud Repository

9. Pull the Code from Cloud Repository.

10.Commit the Code to the Cloud Repository.


1. Create the Repository Locally.

    - Download and Install the GIT.

    Website : https://git-scm.com/download/win

    file name : Git-2.13.1-64-bit.exe

    [Note. Git is the Interface tool used to Interact with the GitHub]

    - Create the Directory Locally.

    Ex.

        D:\demo

    - rigth click on demo folder --->

                                    Select GitBash Here--->

                                                    > git init

    [Note . Automatically demo folder converted as local Repository]


2. Add the User Credentials to the Repository.

     git config --global user.name "Samba"
     git config --global user.email "samba.pendela@gmail.com"


3. Create the Files to the Repository.
    >touch sample.txt
    >git add sample.txt
    >git commit
    >press "i"
    >type "initial commit"
    >press esc
    >type :wq
    >press enter

    From 2nd commit Onwards.
    >git add sample.txt
    >git commit -m "Names Added"


4. Create teh Branch.

    >git branch developer_one
    >git checkout developer_one


5. Merge the Branch

    >git merge developer_one













